{"threadId": "151677ede3b9359a", "messages": [
{"messageId": "151677ede3b9359a", "headers": {"From": "Nitesh Bhutani <bhutani.nishu@gmail.com>", "Date": "Thu, 3 Dec 2015 02:59:04 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] Contirbuting to Opencog - December 2015"}, "body": "I am a recent graduate interested in AI. I have installed opencog and started playing with Python bindings. I am interested in MOSES for Reinforcement Learning, DeSTIN redesign, and Deep Learning perception."},
{"messageId": "151678279f4a5d8f", "headers": {"From": "Ben Goertzel <ben@goertzel.org>", "Date": "Thu, 3 Dec 2015 14:03:01 +0300", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Contirbuting to Opencog - December 2015"}, "body": "It would be great to have you work on MOSES RL but now the best thing would be to do this in Minecraft not Unity3D, we have Minecraft hooks for OpenCog now. Nil Geisweiller can guide you. DeSTIN Redesign is pretty much obsolete. I am in the middle of writing a document clarifying Deep Learning perception."},
{"messageId": "15169adff5833cfe", "headers": {"From": "'Nil Geisweiller' via opencog <opencog@googlegroups.com>", "Date": "Thu, 3 Dec 2015 23:09:41 +0200", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Contirbuting to Opencog - December 2015"}, "body": "That is an ambitious project that would require you to study MOSES and the embodiment code in depth. I am not very familiar with the new embodiment code, but I can certainly guide you through MOSES. Feel free to ping me on Slack."},
{"messageId": "1516c0a048426ec8", "headers": {"From": "Ben Goertzel <ben@goertzel.org>", "Date": "Fri, 4 Dec 2015 09:09:33 +0100", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Contirbuting to Opencog - December 2015"}, "body": "Embodiment is reimplemented now, and the new version is what is used by the Minecraft bridge. A lot may be doable in deep learning via connecting existing python deep learning libraries to OpenCog appropriately."}
]},
