{"messageId": "15157cf998aa22c1", "headers": {"From": "Ben Goertzel <ben@goertzel.org>", "Date": "Mon, 30 Nov 2015 12:53:20 +0300", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Gsoc2016"}, "body": "We do not yet know if OpenCog will be accepted for GSoC 2016, but anyone who has contributed already as a volunteer will tend to get to the front of the list. In late December I plan to better organize TODO tasks for newbies. One interesting project might be improvements to the Pattern Miner. There is also lots to do with NLP pipeline, PLN reasoning engine, and MOSES."},
{"messageId": "1515de891db4baaf", "headers": {"From": "deepthimenon0461@gmail.com", "Date": "Tue, 1 Dec 2015 06:18:19 -0800", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Gsoc2016"}, "body": "Thank you very much for responding Ben will try my best."},
{"messageId": "1515dfc4c5179889", "headers": {"From": "Ben Goertzel <ben@goertzel.org>", "Date": "Tue, 1 Dec 2015 17:39:51 +0300", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] Gsoc2016"}, "body": "Sure. If you have an interest in some specific project or aspect, just let us know on the email list, and we can give you some guidance in that direction."},
